---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AuthorByline from '../../components/AuthorByline.astro';

const title = 'CD Calculator Methodology — Nestfigure';
const description =
  'How Nestfigure’s free CD calculator estimates maturity value: compound-interest formulas, APY conversion, compounding options, and intentional omissions.';
const canonicalPath = '/methodology/cd-calculator/';
const dateLabel = 'July 22, 2026';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'TechArticle',
  headline: 'CD Calculator Methodology',
  description,
  dateModified: '2026-07-22',
  author: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: 'John Rey Balais',
    url: 'https://nestfigure.com/about/',
  },
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'Nestfigure',
    url: 'https://nestfigure.com/',
  },
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  ogImage="/images/feature-cd-calculator.webp"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Methodology · CD</p>
      <h1 class="display" style="font-size:clamp(32px,4.5vw,48px);">CD calculator methodology</h1>
      <p class="lead">Transparent formulas and limits for educational CD estimates.</p>
      <AuthorByline variant="compact" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container prose" style="max-width:720px;">
      <p>
        Tool: <a href="/cd-calculator/">CD calculator</a> · Embed:
        <a href="/embed/cd-calculator/">Embeddable CD calculator</a> · Hub:
        <a href="/methodology/">All methodology</a> · FAQ:
        <a href="/faq/certificate-of-deposit/">CD FAQ</a>
      </p>

      <h2>Purpose</h2>
      <p>
        The CD calculator estimates certificate of deposit maturity value and interest for
        <strong>education</strong>. It is not a bank quote, Truth in Savings disclosure, or personalized advice. U.S.
        deposit products offered by covered institutions must follow Regulation DD (Truth in Savings, 12 CFR Part
        1030); our tool does not replace those disclosures.
      </p>

      <h2>Discrete compounding</h2>
      <p>
        <code class="code">A = P × (1 + r/n)^(n×t)</code>
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>P</strong> — principal</li>
        <li><strong>r</strong> — annual nominal rate (decimal)</li>
        <li><strong>n</strong> — periods per year (365 daily, 12 monthly, 4 quarterly, 2 semi-annual, 1 annual)</li>
        <li><strong>t</strong> — years (term months ÷ 12)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Continuous compounding</h2>
      <p>
        <code class="code">A = P × e^(r×t)</code>
      </p>
      <p>
        Continuous compounding is the mathematical limit of more frequent discrete compounding. It is included for
        completeness; many retail CDs use discrete schedules.
      </p>

      <h2>APY input conversion</h2>
      <p>
        When you enter APY, we convert it to a nominal rate consistent with the selected compounding so that, under this
        model, a one-year horizon matches the entered APY:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Discrete: <code>r = n × ((1 + APY)^(1/n) − 1)</code></li>
        <li>Continuous: <code>r = ln(1 + APY)</code></li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Example: at 4.50% APY for one year with no fees, $10,000 grows by $450 to $10,450 under a pure 4.50% effective
        annual yield—arithmetic under stated assumptions, not a claim about any bank’s current rates.
      </p>

      <h2>Optional monthly deposits</h2>
      <p>
        If you add a monthly deposit, we simulate month-by-month growth then add the deposit. Many traditional CDs do
        not allow add-on deposits; treat this mode as a planning illustration only.
      </p>

      <h2>Outputs</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Final balance, interest earned, total deposited, effective APY under the model</li>
        <li>Growth chart and period schedule</li>
        <li>Compare common terms table</li>
        <li>Copy results and browser PDF export</li>
        <li>Share, embed, and URL prefills</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What we intentionally omit</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Early withdrawal penalties</li>
        <li>Promotional or step-up rates</li>
        <li>Account fees and minimums</li>
        <li>Tax withholding or tax advice</li>
        <li>Issuer-specific day-count rules</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Primary external references</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1030/"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            target="_blank">CFPB — Regulation DD (Truth in Savings)</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/ask-cfpb/what-is-a-certificate-of-deposit-cd-en-917/"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            target="_blank">CFPB — What is a CD?</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.fdic.gov/resources/deposit-insurance/understanding-deposit-insurance"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            target="_blank">FDIC — Deposit insurance</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://ncua.gov/consumers/share-insurance-coverage" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
            >NCUA — Share insurance</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Related content</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/guides/how-cd-interest-works/">How CD interest works</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/cd-vs-savings/">CD vs savings</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/cd-early-withdrawal/">Early withdrawal</a></li>
        <li><a href="/faq/certificate-of-deposit/">CD FAQ</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/">All guides & scenarios</a></li>
      </ul>

      <AuthorByline variant="card" />
      <p class="disclaimer">Last reviewed: {dateLabel}.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    background: #f0f5fe;
    padding: 6px 10px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    display: inline-block;
  }
</style>
